lzh_formatted:
  title: 書懷
  author: 李黿
  language: lzh
  text: 永夜秋蛩閙草根。愁來雙鬢白侵巾。殘生自有悲愁意。不是虫聲易感人。
korean:
  title: 서회
  author: 이원
  language: kor
  text: |-
    긴 밤 가을 귀뚜리 풀뿌리에 들레이고
    시름이 오자 두 귀밑에 흰 것이 침노하네
    이 여생에 시름 본래부터 있었거니
    벌레 우는 그 소리에 새삼 느낀 것 아니로세
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1460_010_0420&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Writing of My Heart
  author: Lee Won
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The long night: autumn crickets clamor through the grass roots.
    When sorrow comes, white streaks creep across my temples.
    In this remaining life, grief has always dwelt within—
    it is not the insect's cry that moves me anew.
  footnotes:
    - The cricket's song is a traditional symbol in East Asian poetry for autumn's melancholy and the passage of time.
    - The white hair at the temples represents both literal aging and the emotional toll of sorrow accumulated over a lifetime.
